OL,5, Plans to raise the state pension age   
OL,6, from 66 should be shelved because we   
OL,7, are not living as long as previously   
OL,8, expected, a new report has suggested.  
OL,10,FCurrent plans would see the age at     
OL,11,Fwhich people are eligible for the state
OL,12,Fpension go up to 67 by 2028, and then  
OL,13,Feventually to 68.                      
OL,15,FConsultant LCP says life expectancy has
OL,16,Fstalled and no changes should be made  
OL,17,Ffor 30 years.                          
OL,19,FThe government has just launched its   
OL,20,Flatest review of the state pension age.
